`sanitize_output` is the last-line redaction applied to *every* model reply before it reaches a user (web chat, SSE stream, OpenAI bridge, tool summaries, voice, REPL). For each secret pattern it calls `find_secret_pattern`, which does a single `text.find(prefix)` — **only the first occurrence** — and then either redacts that one token or gives up. Two consequences: (1) if the first occurrence of a prefix is shorter than `min_len`, the whole pattern aborts and a valid long key *later in the same text* is emitted verbatim; (2) a second, distinct secret sharing the same prefix is never found. On a shared-room household appliance whose stated posture is "shared-room-safe prompt filtering," this defeats the control that is supposed to stop secret leakage.

