## Summary

`WaitingFor` in `crates/engine/src/types/game_state.rs` has 17 variants that represent two identical structural patterns — "player selects objects to pay a cost, then resume" and "player is offered an optional cast" — hard-coded as one variant per cost kind. Adding a new cost keyword today requires touching ~35 files across engine, AI, frontend, and tests. The fix is to parameterize both clusters into 2 variants + 2 supporting enums.

---

## Current state

### Cluster 1: cost-payment (12 variants, lines 2482–2627)

Seven spell-cost variants:

```
DiscardForCost          { player, count, cards[],         pending_cast }
SacrificeForCost        { player, count, min_count, permanents[], pending_cast }
ReturnToHandForCost     { player, count, permanents[],    pending_cast }
