- Every villainous-choice card whose options contrast "that player …" with "you …" is affected (e.g. "they lose 3 life, or you draw a card" templates): the beneficial "you" branch acts on the wrong player.
- Any "you"/"your"-scoped sub-instruction inside the chosen branch (draw, gain life, put onto battlefield, search your library, etc.) is attributed to the chooser, not the controller.

