## Problem

React 19 can introspect or coerce the proxy returned by `createInnerProxy()` and call `valueOf`, `toString`, or `toJSON` on it.

In downstream apps, this can break the proxy at runtime unless those keys return a primitive-friendly function instead of another proxy. We are currently carrying a local patch in the built `@trpc/server` output to special-case those keys.

## Current workaround

```js
if (key === "valueOf" || key === "toString" || key === "toJSON") {
  return function () {
    return "tRPC.proxy(" + path.join(".") + ")";
  };
}
```

## Upstream context

Likely related React bug: https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/35657

## Expected

`@trpc/server` should handle these coercion keys in `createInnerProxy()` so downstream apps do not need to keep a `patch-package` workaround across `@11.x` upgrades.

